<h1 id="more_info_section">More information about the pilot project Open Ricgraph demo server</h1>
To learn more about the Pilot project Open Ricgraph demo server,
including how to participate, please read the
<a href="https://www.ricgraph.eu/pilot-project-open-ricgraph-demo-server.html"
   target="_blank">Pilot project Open Ricgraph demo server</a>
webpage, or contact
<a href="https://www.ricgraph.eu/contact.html"
   target="_blank">Rik D.T. Janssen</a>
from Utrecht University.

<h2>Organizations and sources harvested</h2>
This Open Ricgraph demo server
contains research information harvested for
<a href="https://www.amsterdamumc.org/en/research.htm"
   target="_blank">Amsterdam University Medical Centers (AUMC)</a> and for
<a href="https://www.tudelft.nl/en"
   target="_blank">Delft University of Technology (DUT)</a>.
It is harvested from the
Research Information System
<a href="https://www.elsevier.com/solutions/pure"
   target="_blank">Pure</a>
(<a href="https://pure.amsterdamumc.nl"
    target="_blank">access AUMC Pure</a>,
<a href="https://research.tudelft.nl/en"
   target="_blank">access DUT Pure</a>),
the meta data aggregator
<a href="https://openalex.org"
   target="_blank">OpenAlex</a>, and
the research software repository
<a href="https://research-software-directory.org"
   target="_blank">Research Software Directory</a>.
Research information from Pure and OpenAlex is from years 2022 - 2026,
from the Research Software Directory from all years.

<h2>What to do if you would like to have your information removed from Ricgraph</h2>
All information in the Open Ricgraph demo server is publicly
available in those source systems.
However, if you find your information listed in Ricgraph
and want it removed, you can request deletion by email.
Please specify exactly what you'd like to have removed.
Use the email address corresponding to the value in the
<em>_source</em> column for the items you want removed:
<ul>
    <li>
        If the value ends with <em>-AUMC</em>, email
        <a href="mailto:privacy@amsterdamumc.nl"
           target="_blank">privacy@amsterdamumc.nl</a>.
        For more details, please read the
        <a href="https://www.amsterdamumc.org/en/general-privacy-statement-of-amsterdam-umc.htm"
           target="_blank">General privacy statement of Amsterdam UMC</a>.
    <li>
        If the value ends with <em>-DUT</em>, email
        <a href="mailto:privacy-tud@tudelft.nl"
           target="_blank">privacy-tud@tudelft.nl</a>.
        For more details, please read the
        <a href="https://www.tudelft.nl/en/privacy-statement"
           target="_blank">Privacy statement of the Delft University of Technology</a>.
    <li>
        If you see both endings (<em>-AUMC</em> and <em>-DUT</em>),
        you may contact either email address.
    </li>
</ul>
